00022 /* The bits in the feature bits field are set to identify the features to be used
00023  * for that particular session. To indicate that more than one feature is
00024  * supported, the target will bitwise "OR" the supported feature values to compute
00025  * the value of the field. The target’s set of supported feature bits will be
00026  * bitwise "ANDED" together with the host’s set of requested feature bits, and the
00027  * result will be used for the session.
00028  */
00029 #define SSDP_HELLO_PKT_UNCOMPRESSED_FEATURE_BIT             0x00000001
00030 #define SSDP_HELLO_PKT_NAND_BOOTABLE_IMAGE_FEATURE_BIT      0x00000002
00031 #define SSDP_HELLO_PKT_NAND_BOOTLOADER_FEATURE_BIT          0x00000004
00032 #define SSDP_HELLO_PKT_NAND_MULTI_IMAGE_FEATURE_BIT         0x00000008
00033 #define SSDP_HELLO_PKT_UNFRAMED_STREAMING_DATA_FEATURE_BIT  0x00000010
00034 #define SSDP_HELLO_PKT_QDL_HIGH_SPEED_FEATURE_BIT           0x00000020
00035 #define SSDP_HELLO_PKT_QDL_BOOT_AND_RECOVERY_FEATURE_BIT    0x00000040
